        "lang": "cht",
        "text": "你們說：神為惡人的兒女積蓄罪孽； 我說：不如本人受報，好使他親自知道。"
      },
      "esv": {
        "version_id": "ESV",
        "version_name": "English Standard Version",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "You say, ‘God stores up their iniquity for their children.’ Let him pay it out to them, that they may know it."
      },
      "nasb": {
        "version_id": "NASB",
        "version_name": "New American Standard Bible",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "You say, ‘God stores away a man’s iniquity for his sons.’ Let God repay him so that he may know it."
      },
      "niv": {
        "version_id": "NIV",
        "version_name": "New International Version",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "It is said, ‘God stores up the punishment of the wicked for their children.’ Let him repay the wicked, so that they themselves will experience it!"
      },
      "nkjv": {
        "version_id": "NKJV",
        "version_name": "New King James Version",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "They  say, ‘God lays up one’s iniquity for his children’; Let Him recompense him, that he may know it."
      },
      "nlt": {
        "version_id": "NLT",
        "version_name": "New Living Translation",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "“‘Well,’ you say, ‘at least God will punish their children!’ But I say he should punish the ones who sin, so that they understand his judgment."
      }
